<title>TANZANIA: U.N. Rwanda court adjourns, hears massacre witness.</title>
<headline>U.N. Rwanda court adjourns, hears massacre witness.</headline>
<dateline>ARUSHA, Tanzania 1997-01-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>The U.N. Rwanda war crimes tribunal adjourned late on Friday after hearing three hours of chilling testimony by the first genocide witness to appear before the court.</p>
<p>Presiding judge Laity Kama of Senegal said the trial of Hutu former government official Jean-Paul Akayesu would resume on Monday. The court heard testimony from a Tutsi woman who had worked for Akayesu as an accountant and described how he ordered the slaughter of Tutsis during the 1994 genocide.</p>
